# Order matters — Netlify processes this file top-to-bottom, first match wins.
# This file also takes precedence over netlify.toml redirects, so the proxy
# rules MUST be declared here too, not only in netlify.toml (where they were
# previously shadowed by the SPA catchall below).

# Backend proxy — forward /api/* and /auth/* to the Render API so cookies
# are first-party on racingplanner.netlify.app (see netlify.toml for the
# full Safari-ITP explanation). The `!` force flag makes the rule win
# even against a shadow file, belt-and-suspenders.
/api/*   https://racingplanner-api.onrender.com/api/:splat   200!
/auth/*  https://racingplanner-api.onrender.com/auth/:splat  200!

# SPA fallback — any path the client router should handle gets index.html.
/*  /index.html  200
